# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Supabase Connection Strings Reference
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Use the appropriate connection string based on your use case
# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Database
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── For Production Runtime (Backend on Render) ───────────────
# USE THIS: Connection pooling via PgBouncer (Port 6543)
# Best for: NestJS backend running on Render
# Why: Manages connections efficiently, prevents pool exhaustion
DATABASE_URL_POOLED=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1

# ─── For Migrations & Schema Changes ──────────────────────────
# USE THIS: Direct connection (Port 5432)
# Best for: Running Prisma migrations, db push, db seed
# Why: Prisma Migrate requires direct database access
DATABASE_URL_DIRECT=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres

# ─── For Local Development ────────────────────────────────────
# USE THIS: Direct connection with SSL mode (Port 5432)
# Best for: Local development with Supabase cloud database
DATABASE_URL_DEV=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?sslmode=require

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# How to Get Your Connection Strings
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Settings (⚙️) → Database
# 4. Scroll to "Connection string" section
# 5. Select "URI" tab
# 6. Copy the connection string
# 7. Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] with your database password
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Usage Guidelines
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. PRODUCTION (Render Backend):
#    - Use DATABASE_URL_POOLED
#    - Set in Render Environment Variables as DATABASE_URL
#    - Includes pgbouncer=true for connection pooling
#    - Includes connection_limit=1 to prevent exhaustion

# 2. RUNNING MIGRATIONS:
#    - Use DATABASE_URL_DIRECT locally
#    - Run: DATABASE_URL="[DIRECT_URL]" npx prisma migrate deploy
#    - DO NOT use pooled connection for migrations
#    - Prisma Migrate requires direct database access

# 3. LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
#    - Use DATABASE_URL_DEV in backend/.env
#    - Includes sslmode=require for secure connection
#    - Use direct connection (port 5432)

